\subsection{Hybrid Optimization Strategy}
\label{subsec:optimization}
The PQC was trained using a classical optimization loop \cite{cerezo2021variational} to find the optimal circuit parameters $(\tau_{\text{opt}}, \theta_{\text{opt}})$ that minimize a cost function based on the Kullback-Leibler (KL) divergence \cite{kullback1951information}. A KL divergence of zero in our results indicates that the quantum circuit has perfectly captured the biological mechanism of ligand-receptor binding.

